text: A dual uniform polyhedron is the dual of a uniform polyhedron. Just like a uniform polyhedron is vertex-transitive, a dual uniform polyhedron is face- transitive. {| class=wikitable !Uniform set ||Dual uniform set |- align=center |5 Platonic solids || 5 Platonic solids |- align=center |4 Kepler solids || 4 Kepler solids |- align=center | 13 Archimedean solids || 13 Catalan solids |- align=center | ∞ Prisms||∞ Bipyramids |- align=center |∞ Antiprisms||∞ Trapezohedra |- align=center |53 nonregular uniform star polyhedra||53 dual uniform star polyhedra |} == Example == * List of uniform polyhedra ==References== * *
